						<summary>

						<p>ĀṞAGAḶŪR, ATTUR TALUK, SALEM DISTRICT.</p>						

						<p>Kāmēśvara temple, central shrine, north base</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Ramanātha-dēvar Year 13.</hi></p>						

						<p>Records the grant of the village Nāṭṭāmaṅgalam in Śela-nāḍu, given to him as <hi rend="italic">jīvitam,</hi> as <hi rend="italic">dēvadāṉam-iṟai-ili</hi> (i.e) (land freed from taxes on account of its being a grant to God) to God Tirukāmēśvaram-uḍaiya-nāyaṉār by Rāguttarāmaṉ. The grant implied the inclusion of the right to the wet and dry lands in the village as also to the dues on account of <hi rend="italic">kaḍamai</hi> and <hi rend="italic">iṟai-muṟaimai.</hi></p>						

						</summary>
